            <section xml:id="d0/da1/classmpx_1_1_mpx_running_context_1_1_mpx_signal_context_1ad8f814acf0e6d8f1e1b7ed9b735237ac">
                <title>mpx::MpxRunningContext::MpxSignalContext::MpxSignalContext (MpxRunningContext *ctx, int signo, sigfunc f, ctx_appdt_t appdata)</title> <emphasis>create signal handler</emphasis>
                
<para>function saves following informations in newly created instance of signal handler:</para>

<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>ctx - reference to instance of I/O multiplexer which created signal handler. It will be used by signal delivery to select correct I/O multiplexer when redirecting signals</para>
</listitem><listitem>
<para>signo - number of signal to be handled by this handler</para>
</listitem><listitem>
<para>f - call-back function to be used when handling signal</para>
</listitem><listitem>
<para>appdata - general reference to data provided by application </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>

            </section>
